Create a file name package.json
And write this into this code

{
  "name": "my-project",
  "version": "1.0.0",
  "description": "My project description",
  "dependencies": {
    "discord.js": "^13.0.0"
  },
  "scripts": {
    "start": "node index.js"
  },
  "author": "Your Name",
  "license": "MIT"
}

save it.

Create a new file and name it node_modules.json

and write this into the file

npm install discord.js

and save it.

Now there are three file which includes script, package, modules, and zip it with the hosting file.
